metadata.author: SIO/Yoon Lee and Chloe Jenniches
metadata.description: This protocol is designed to perform end-to-end fully automated in situ hybridizations for 48 samples (wells) each containing probes for four targets. The biological sample type is the embryo of sea urchin Lytechinus pictus. The estimated duration of this protocol is 28 hours. This means that if the protocol is started in the morning (08:00-12:00), samples should be ready to image in the afternoon (12:00-16:00) of the following day.
